article.headline: Utah State 74, San Francisco 48
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Spencer Nelson scored 20 points to lead Utah State Aggies to a 74-48 victory over the San Francisco Dons in the Gossner Foods Holiday Classic Monday night. Nelson went into the game averaging 11 points per game. Against San Francisco, Nelson was 7-of-8 on field goals and 6-for-8 from the free-throw line. Utah State (7-1) led by as many as 29 when Tyler Williams notched a 3-point shot with a little under two minutes left in the game. Only Dommanic Ingerson scored in double digits for San Francisco (8-6) with 14. Utah State led 38-19 at the half, thanks in part to Nate Harris' slam dunk with just 15 seconds left. Utah State scored first with a three-point play by Nelson and never fell behind for the rest of the game. Utah State will meet New Mexico State in the championship game Tuesday night. The consolation game will feature the Texas-San Antonio against San Francisco. In the earlier game Monday night, New Mexico State beat Texas-San Antonio, 62-53. Utah State remains undefeated, boasting a 18-0 record during the 10-year history of the Gossner Foods Classic.
